headline: Energy Transition Today - Solar Energy Projects Boost Sustainability in Long Island Schools
summary: SUNation Energy, Inc. has entered Letters of Intent with Energy Systems Group for the development of solar projects totaling over 2.35 megawatts (MW) at two school districts on Long Island, New York. The proposed installations aim to deliver renewable solar energy across ten buildings, with a generation of over 3 megawatt hours annually, effectively offsetting a significant portion of the districts' energy requirements.
